 ('157', '118', '2', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"We\'re building our own building\",\"slug\":\"were-building-our-own-building\",\"postDate\":1478209431,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"55\":\"#000000\",\"56\":[\"117\"],\"54\":[\"111\"],\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"centeredText\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Together with our brand strategy partners at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/stokestrategy.com\\/\\\">Stoke,<\\/a>&nbsp;Turnstyle is breaking ground on a new 5,000 sq. foot office in August 2016. The building will serve as home for 20+ strategists, designers and developers. Located on Canal Street, the park-side project borders the Burke-Gilman Trail and overlooks the Fremont Cut waterway. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\\"The firms continue to grow, and our need for space was at odds with the long-term lease trends of Seattle,\\u201d said Stoke partner Erin Quick. \\u201cIt makes good financial sense for the businesses, and for the firms\\u2019 practices. We\\u2019re creating a unique place where creative thinkers can do their best work, and clients can collaborate with us in new and different ways.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On the street level, a cafe-style collaboration space serves as a foundation to two levels with open-floor studios and meeting space. Designed with 16\\u2019 floor-to-ceiling windows, the plan takes advantage of the views over the trail and canal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\u201cThe work areas will be bathed with natural light. An open atrium at the center creates visual interest, with the benefit of passive solar design,\\u201d said Ben Graham, partner at Turnstyle. \\u201cIt\'s a design-friendly environment that makes the best of our open, collaborative work style.\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\u201cThe commercial office market is racing, and the long-term value for buyers in Seattle looks good,\\u201d noted Graham. \\u201cAs the business environment accelerates, having a place that minimizes our commutes, offers easy access to downtown, with everyday access to great restaurants, and enhances mobility options on the Burke-Gilman Trail \\u2013 all with a deck and a view \\u2013 seemed like a winning combination.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The architecture was led by award-winning&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/heliotropearchitects.com\\/\\\">Heliotrope,<\\/a>&nbsp;of Ballard. Seattle\\u2019s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/westernventures.com\\/\\\">Western Ventures<\\/a>serves as the general contractor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Construction is targeted for completion in June, 2017.<\\/p>\",\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\"}}}}}', '2016-11-03 21:43:51', '2016-11-03 21:43:51', 'ea2982b6-1dbd-4bf4-9669-0dc75d21875e'),
 ('158', '122', '2', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Turnstyle principal serves as juror for communication arts design annual\",\"slug\":\"turnstyle-principal-serves-as-juror-for-communication-arts-design-annual\",\"postDate\":1478209624,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"55\":\"#ff7fc5\",\"56\":[\"121\"],\"54\":[\"111\"],\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"centeredText\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Turnstyle principal and creative director Steven Watson was invited to serve as a juror for Communication Arts magazine\\u2019s 56th Annual Design Competition. Communication Arts is a professional journal for designers, art directors, design firms, corporate design departments, agencies and everyone involved in visual communications. The CA Design Annual, published each September,&nbsp;is one of the most respected competitions in our industry.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Of the 4,083 entries to the 56th Design Annual, only 153 were accepted, representing the work of 141 designers, design firms and in-house design departments, making the Design Annual the most exclusive major design competition in the world. Entries were selected on the basis of creative excellence and quality of execution.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Steve screened entries along with five other jurors: Kelly Bjork (VSA Partners), Dora Drimalas (Hybrid-Design), Jay Fletcher (J Fletcher Deisgn), Jeffrey Keyton (MTV), and Jean Coyne (executive editor of Communication Arts magazine). It was an honor to be asked to participate alongside such accomplished fellow jurors.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In the column that accompanies the design competition, Steve was asked for his point of view on the entries and the design trends they represent. He replied that \\u201ctechnology will continue to change how we consume media, images, and messages. But the underlying principles of design will always be relevant in communicating effectively, regardless of how the future evolves.\\u201d<\\/p>\",\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"insetImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"120\"],\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\"}}}}}', '2016-11-03 21:47:05', '2016-11-03 21:47:05', 'ac4ff672-87b5-4ec9-9ab5-cab75ae0dfa9'),
 ('159', '122', '2', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Turnstyle Principal Serves as Juror for Communication Arts Design Annual\",\"slug\":\"turnstyle-principal-serves-as-juror-for-communication-arts-design-annual\",\"postDate\":1478209620,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"55\":\"#ff7fc5\",\"56\":[\"121\"],\"54\":[\"111\"],\"10\":{\"123\":{\"type\":\"centeredText\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Turnstyle principal and creative director Steven Watson was invited to serve as a juror for Communication Arts magazine\\u2019s 56th Annual Design Competition. Communication Arts is a professional journal for designers, art directors, design firms, corporate design departments, agencies and everyone involved in visual communications. The CA Design Annual, published each September,&nbsp;is one of the most respected competitions in our industry.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Of the 4,083 entries to the 56th Design Annual, only 153 were accepted, representing the work of 141 designers, design firms and in-house design departments, making the Design Annual the most exclusive major design competition in the world. Entries were selected on the basis of creative excellence and quality of execution.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Steve screened entries along with five other jurors: Kelly Bjork (VSA Partners), Dora Drimalas (Hybrid-Design), Jay Fletcher (J Fletcher Deisgn), Jeffrey Keyton (MTV), and Jean Coyne (executive editor of Communication Arts magazine). It was an honor to be asked to participate alongside such accomplished fellow jurors.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>In the column that accompanies the design competition, Steve was asked for his point of view on the entries and the design trends they represent. He replied that \\u201ctechnology will continue to change how we consume media, images, and messages. But the underlying principles of design will always be relevant in communicating effectively, regardless of how the future evolves.\\u201d<\\/p>\",\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\"}},\"124\":{\"type\":\"insetImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"120\"],\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\"}}}}}', '2016-11-03 21:58:08', '2016-11-03 21:58:08', '7782dad4-6d64-49f5-9c96-70f8614a8ce1'),
 ('160', '118', '2', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"We\'re Building Our Own Building\",\"slug\":\"were-building-our-own-building\",\"postDate\":1478209380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"55\":\"#000000\",\"56\":[\"117\"],\"54\":[\"111\"],\"10\":{\"119\":{\"type\":\"centeredText\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Together with our brand strategy partners at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/stokestrategy.com\\/\\\">Stoke,<\\/a>&nbsp;Turnstyle is breaking ground on a new 5,000 sq. foot office in August 2016. The building will serve as home for 20+ strategists, designers and developers. Located on Canal Street, the park-side project borders the Burke-Gilman Trail and overlooks the Fremont Cut waterway. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\\"The firms continue to grow, and our need for space was at odds with the long-term lease trends of Seattle,\\u201d said Stoke partner Erin Quick. \\u201cIt makes good financial sense for the businesses, and for the firms\\u2019 practices. We\\u2019re creating a unique place where creative thinkers can do their best work, and clients can collaborate with us in new and different ways.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>On the street level, a cafe-style collaboration space serves as a foundation to two levels with open-floor studios and meeting space. Designed with 16\\u2019 floor-to-ceiling windows, the plan takes advantage of the views over the trail and canal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\u201cThe work areas will be bathed with natural light. An open atrium at the center creates visual interest, with the benefit of passive solar design,\\u201d said Ben Graham, partner at Turnstyle. \\u201cIt\'s a design-friendly environment that makes the best of our open, collaborative work style.\\u201d&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\u201cThe commercial office market is racing, and the long-term value for buyers in Seattle looks good,\\u201d noted Graham. \\u201cAs the business environment accelerates, having a place that minimizes our commutes, offers easy access to downtown, with everyday access to great restaurants, and enhances mobility options on the Burke-Gilman Trail \\u2013 all with a deck and a view \\u2013 seemed like a winning combination.\\u201d<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The architecture was led by award-winning&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/heliotropearchitects.com\\/\\\">Heliotrope,<\\/a>&nbsp;of Ballard. Seattle\\u2019s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/westernventures.com\\/\\\">Western Ventures<\\/a>serves as the general contractor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Construction is targeted for completion in June, 2017.<\\/p>\",\"verticalSpacingLevel\":\"vertical-spacing-0\"}}}}}', '2016-11-03 21:58:27', '2016-11-03 21:58:27', '06562b99-c649-437c-badb-d9252e480806'),
