 ('19', '104', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '<p class=\"h3 med\"><span class=\"white\">STYLE<br>IS A<br>SIMPLE<br>WAY<br>OF<br>SAYING<br>COMPLEX<br>THINGS<br></span><span class=\"blue\">&mdash;JEAN<br>COCTEAU</span></p>', '<p class=\"large\"><span class=\"white\"><span></span>Style is Not a&nbsp;4-letter Word<span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"large\"><span class=\"white\"><span></span>In our experience, the brands that are the most magnetic are those which project distinct, memorable and charismatic personalities. These brands place equal emphasis on what they say and how they say it. Some design purists might say that style is merely artificial decoration that should be avoided in favor of logic&mdash;“form follows function” and all that. Don’t get us wrong, we’re not proponents of style for its own sake, or as ornament applied after an idea has already been defined. Rather, we employ style as an integral and strategic component of our brand-development process. At its best, style can be that magical something about a company or product that pulls people in and transcends the logical. So, to us, style is not a 4-letter word. On the contrary, we embrace it, harnessing its power to cut through the clutter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"large\"><span class=\"white\">And besides, “style” has five letters.</span></p>', '#000000', 'vertical-spacing-2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-11-02 23:38:39', '2016-11-22 20:42:26', '8d4c75d3-9de1-48ae-87fb-a6d3a971ec49'),
